cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DM, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a new method for imbalanced data classification using graphs and sampling techniques. This falls under the broad category of machine learning and data mining (cs.LG), as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of graphs and proximity information also suggests a possible fit with the sub-category of data mining (cs.DM). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of the proposed method for image classification, which could potentially fall under computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the use of sampling techniques and the focus on classification suggests a possible fit with neural networks (cs.NE).
